YOUNGSTERS got a chance to practise their language skills by setting up a fundraising French cafe in their school. Pupils' cafe is talk of town - in French YOUNGSTERS got a chance to practise their language skills by setting up a fundraising French cafe in their school.Christie Park Primary in Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire, won funding for the European Languages Day event and used the cafe to help Macmillan Cancer Support.Every P1 pupil who started school last month is being introduced to a foreign language in their first year at school and will learn a second language by P5. Pupils will continue learning their additional languages until 2020, when they will be in S3.The council received &pound;93,000 from the Scottish Government for the policy and for teacher training. 